         <abstract>
            <p>Proof is given that the weight functions $w(x, p) = 1/[\pi(p + x)\sqrt{x(1 - x)}]$ on (0, 1) admit Chebyshev quadratures for any fixed $p \geqslant 1$, and every $N$. For the particular cases when $p = 1$ and $p = 2$, the nodes are tabulated to ten decimal places for $N$-point rules with $N = 2, 4, 6, 8$, and 12. Numerical tables are also given for a coefficient in the expression of the error term.</p>
          </abstract>
